00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:25,080
这是什么时候的事
When was this?

363
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:27,600
昨天早上
Yesterday morning.

364
00:12:28,430 --> 00:12:30,490
那个新娘的脸  是怎样描述的
The bride's face, how was it described?

365
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:37,980
"像死人一样苍白  嘴像一道绯红的伤口"
"White as death, mouth like a crimson wound."

366
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:43,280
这是创作还是事实
Poetry or truth?

367
00:12:44,310 --> 00:12:45,870
很多人会说它们是一样的
Many would say they're the same thing.

368
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:48,630
对  他们都是白痴  创作还是事实
Yes, idiots. Poetry or truth?

369
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:53,170
我看到过她的脸  是在后来
I saw her face myself. Afterwards.

370
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:54,750
什么的后来
After what?

371
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:55,820
你
You?

372
00:12:58,510 --> 00:12:59,760
还是我
Or me?

373
00:13:06,190 --> 00:13:09,160
不是吧  雷斯垂德  一个女人当众饮弹
Oh, really, Lestrade, a woman blows her own brains out in public

374
00:13:09,170 --> 00:13:11,600
而你需要我帮助找出罪犯
and you need help identifying the guilty party?

375
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:14,650
恐怕苏格兰场又刷低了下限
I feel Scotland Yard has reached a new low.

376
00:13:14,910 --> 00:13:16,340
那不是我来的原因
That's not why I'm here.

377
00:13:16,340 --> 00:13:18,980
-我猜也是  -她叫什么名字  那个新娘
- I surmised. - What was her name, the bride?

378
00:13:19,630 --> 00:13:22,460
艾米丽娅·瑞克莱蒂  昨天是她的结婚纪念日
Emelia Ricoletti. Yesterday was her wedding anniversary.

379
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:24,800
当然  有人报了警
The police, of course, were called.

380
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:28,040
她的尸体被送到了停尸房
And her body taken to the morgue.

381
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:31,000
这是标准程序  你为什么要告诉我们这些
Standard procedure. Why are you telling us what may be presumed?

382
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:34,420
因为接下来发生的事
Because of what happened next.

383
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:39,640
在莱姆豪斯  就几小时之后
Limehouse. Just a few hours later.

384
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:54,780
托马斯·瑞克莱蒂  艾米丽娅·瑞克莱蒂的丈夫
Thomas Ricoletti. Emelia Ricoletti's husband.

385
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:58,450
大概是在去停尸房辨认遗体的路上吧
Presumably on his way to the morgue to identify her remains?

386
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,770
结果他省了这麻烦
As it turned out, he was saved the trip.

387
00:14:08,570 --> 00:14:13,040
*别忘了我*
*Do not forget me*

388
00:14:13,410 --> 00:14:17,330
*别忘了我*
*Do not forget me*

389
00:14:17,970 --> 00:14:20,970
{\an8}*记住那少女*
*Remember the maid...*

390
00:14:20,470 --> 00:14:21,650
你是谁
Who are you?

391
00:14:21,970 --> 00:14:25,130
{\an8}*磨坊的少女*
*The maid of the mill...*

392
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:25,890
你为什么要这样做  告诉我你是谁
Why are you doing this? Just tell me who you are!

393
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:29,130
你听出了我们的歌吗  亲爱的
You recognise our song, my dear?

394
00:14:29,940 --> 00:14:32,090
我在婚礼上唱过
I sang it at our wedding.

395
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:38,040
艾米丽娅
Emelia?

396
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:42,490
你死了  你不可能在这里  你死了
You, you're dead, you can't be here, you died!

397
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:45,230
我美吗  托马斯
Am I not beautiful, Thomas?

398
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,410
跟你娶我那天一样美
As beautiful as the day you married me?

399
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:50,300
-谁...  -这是怎么回事
- Who... - What the hell is all this about?!

400
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:55,720
看起来像是什么样  我英俊的朋友
What does it look like, my handsome friend?

401
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,500
这是"枪杆"下的婚姻
It's a shotgun wedding.

402
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:11,810
不至死亡  永不分离  他们各死了一次
Till death us do part. Twice in this case.

403
00:15:28,980 --> 00:15:30,100
真离奇
Extraordinary.

404
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:32,380
不可能
Impossible.

405
00:15:33,020 --> 00:15:33,720
太棒了
Superb.

406
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,520
在街头自杀  被尸体谋杀
Suicide as street theatre, murder by corpse.

407
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:36,710
雷斯垂德  你简直宠坏我们了
Lestrade, you're spoiling us.

408
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:37,860
华生  你的帽子和外套
Watson, your hat and coat.

409
00:15:37,860 --> 00:15:39,020
-我们去哪里  -停尸房
- Where are we going? - To the morgue.

410
00:15:39,030 --> 00:15:40,450
一刻也不能耽搁了
There's not a moment to lose,

411
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,030
很少有人会这样说停尸房
which one can so rarely say of a morgue.

412
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,160
那我就坐在这里吗
And am I just to sit here?

413
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:46,880
当然不是  亲爱的  我们之后会饿的
Not at all, my dear. We'll be hungry later.

414
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,490
福尔摩斯  有个问题  穿花呢衣服去停尸房吗
Holmes, just one thing, tweeds in a morgue?

415
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:51,860
没时间换衣服了  华生
Needs must when the devil drives, Watson.

416
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,080
太太
Ma'am.

417
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,720
我参与了一项活动
I'm part of a campaign, you know.

418
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:00,050
活动
Oh, campaign?

419
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:01,720
为女性争取投票权
Votes for women.

420
00:16:02,410 --> 00:16:04,840
你是支持还是反对
And are you for or against?

421
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,400
出去
Get out.

422
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:23,670
他们又走了  对吧
Have they gone off again, have they?

423
00:16:24,270 --> 00:16:27,630
那些绅士过着什么样的生活啊
I don't know, what a life those gentlemen lead.

424
00:16:27,630 --> 00:16:30,400
是啊  那些绅士
Yes. Those gentlemen!

425
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,260
算了
Never you mind.

426
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:35,040
差点忘了  这是给你的
Almost forgot, that came for you.

427
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:47,770
赫德森太太  告诉我丈夫我会晚归
Mrs Hudson, tell my husband I'll be home late,

428
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,890
我有些急事
I have some urgent business.

429
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:51,230
一切还好吧
Is everything all right?

430
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:54,230
只是一个需要帮助的朋友
Oh, you know, just a, er, friend in need.

431
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:56,280
天啊  什么朋友
Oh, dear. What friend?

432
00:16:57,010 --> 00:16:58,160
英格兰
England.

433
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:04,020
还真是含糊
Well, that's not very specific.

434
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:08,810
停尸房谁当班
Who's on mortuary duty?

435
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,020
你知道的
You know who.

436
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:12,370
总是他
Always him.

437
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:21,710
拜托告诉我是哪个傻瓜干的
Please tell me which idiot did this!

438
00:17:24,660 --> 00:17:26,690
这是为了大家的安全
It's for everyone's safety.

439
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:31,960
这女人死了  她半边头都不见了
This woman is dead, half her head is missing.

440
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,640
她对谁都不是威胁
She's not a threat to anyone.

441
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:36,660
跟她的丈夫说去吧  他在那边的罩单下
Tell that to her husband, he's under a sheet over there.

442
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:37,990
不管昨晚在莱姆豪斯发生了什么
Whatever happened in Limehouse last night,

443
00:17:37,990 --> 00:17:41,110
我们能断定那不是一个死去的女人干的
I think we can safely assume it wasn't the work of a dead woman.

444
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:43,640
比这更奇怪的事都发生过
Stranger things have happened.

445
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:45,210
比如呢
Such as...?

446
00:17:45,530 --> 00:17:48,550
奇怪的事
Well... Strange things.

447
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:50,080
你说话跟小孩一样
You're speaking like a child.

448
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:52,190
这显然是活人干的  他在哪里
This is clearly man's work. Where is he?

449
00:17:56,740 --> 00:17:57,750
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

450
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:00,900
霍普
Hooper.

451
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:06,210
你  继续工作
You, back to work!

452
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:11,880
你是来用魔术震撼我们了吧
So, come to astonish us with your magic tricks, I suppose?

453
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:14,040
你想提醒我注意什么事吗
Is there anything to which you would like to draw my attention?

454
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,820
完全没有  福尔摩斯先生
Nothing at all, Mr Holmes.

455
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:18,940
你想什么时候走都行
You may leave any time you like.

456
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:22,360
霍普医生  是我请福尔摩斯先生来的  合作点
Dr Hooper, I asked Mr Holmes to come here. Cooperate.

457
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:23,580
这是命令
That's an order.

458
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:27,490
有两点"值得注意"
There are two "Features of interest",

459
00:18:27,490 --> 00:18:30,150
正如你在华生医生的故事里经常说的
as you are always saying in Dr Watson's stories.

460
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:31,240
我从来没说过
I never say that.

461
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,780
你说过  很多次
You do, actually, quite a lot.

462
00:18:34,860 --> 00:18:37,630
首先  这绝对是艾米丽娅·瑞克莱蒂
First of all, this is definitely Emelia Ricoletti.

463
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:39,440
她已经被确定身份了
She has been categorically identified.

464
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,630
这肯定是她  无可置疑
Beyond a doubt, it is her.

465
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,570
那昨晚在莱姆豪斯是谁
Then who was that in Limehouse last night?

466
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,600
也是艾米丽娅·瑞克莱蒂
That was also Emelia Ricoletti.

467
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:47,030
不可能  她死了  躺在这里
It can't have been. She was dead, she was here.

468
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:49,410
是她自己的丈夫
She was positively identified

469
00:18:49,410 --> 00:18:51,930
在死去的前几秒确认的
by her own husband, seconds before he died.

470
00:18:51,950 --> 00:18:54,690
他没理由撒谎  几乎不可能搞错
He had no reason to lie, could hardly have been mistaken.

471
00:18:54,690 --> 00:18:57,320
车夫也认识她  那就是她
The cabbie knew her, too, there's no question it's her.

472
00:18:57,470 --> 00:19:01,340
但她不可能同时出现在两个地方  对吧
But she can't have been in two places at the same time, can she?

473
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:03,140
不  华生  对于刚死的人来说
No, Watson, one place is strictly the limit

474
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:04,580
他们只能去一个地方
for the recently deceased.

475
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:05,570
福尔摩斯
Holmes!

476
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:07,540
-可能是双胞胎吗  -不
- Could it have been twins? - No.

477
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:08,240
为什么
Why not?

478
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:10,140
因为从来都不是双胞胎
Because it's never twins.

479
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:12,330
艾米丽娅没有双胞胎  也没有姐妹
Emelia was not a twin, nor did she have any sisters.

480
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:14,940
她有一个哥哥  四年前去世了
She had one older brother who died four years ago.

481
00:19:14,940 --> 00:19:18,690
也许是秘密的双胞胎
Hmm, maybe it was a secret twin.

482
00:19:19,210 --> 00:19:20,110
什么
A what?!

483
00:19:20,370 --> 00:19:22,300
秘密的双胞胎
A secret twin.

484
00:19:23,780 --> 00:19:24,680
知道吗
Hmm? You know?

485
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,080
没人知道的双胞胎
A twin that nobody knows about.

486
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:27,730
这一切可能是策划好的
This whole thing could have been planned.

487
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,690
从怀孕时开始
Since the moment of conception.

488
00:19:29,690 --> 00:19:31,720
她真是太有先见之明了
How breathtakingly prescient of her.

489
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,700
从来不是双胞胎  华生
It is never twins, Watson!

490
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:34,810
那你怎么看
Then what's your theory?

491
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:37,540
更重要的是  你什么毛病
More to the point, what's your problem?

492
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,310
-我不明白  -你为什么这么害怕
- I, I don't understand... - Why were you so frightened?

493
00:19:40,310 --> 00:19:42,800
到现在为止  没什么能说明你为什么要喝酒
Nothing so far has justified your assault on my decanter,

494
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:45,250
还有为什么允许一个死去的女人被逮捕
and why have you allowed a dead woman to be placed under arrest?

495
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:48,190
因为还有一点"值得注意"
Ah, that would be the other feature of interest.

496
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:52,500
她指尖上有一些血迹
A smear of blood on her finger.

497
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,610
血迹的由来可以有多种解释
That could have happened any number of ways.

498
00:19:54,650 --> 00:19:55,820
没错
Indeed.

499
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:57,940
还有一点
There's one other thing.

500
00:19:58,350 --> 00:20:00,070
之前没有血迹
It wasn't there earlier.

501
00:20:01,670 --> 00:20:03,510
那个也是新的
Neither was that.

502
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:14,210
你
You!

503
00:20:14,470 --> 00:20:15,510
你
You?

504
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:17,370
你
You?!

505
00:20:17,370 --> 00:20:18,360
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

506
00:20:20,660 --> 00:20:24,560
吞枪自尽  子弹贯穿头部...
Gun in the mouth, a bullet through the brain...

507
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:28,730
后脑被轰掉
Back of the head blown clean off.

508
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:32,460
他是怎么活下来的
How could he survive?

509
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:36,110
你是说"她"吧
"She", you mean.

510
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,070
什么
I'm sorry?

511
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:39,490
不是"他"  是"她"
Not "He", "She".

512
00:20:39,570 --> 00:20:41,380
是  当然了
Yes, yes of course.

513
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:45,700
谢谢你们给了我这么吸引人的案子
Well, thank you all for a fascinating case.

514
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:48,430
我破案之后会给你们发电报的  华生
I'll send you a telegram when I've solved it. Watson.

515
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:53,330
死因明显是枪伤
The gunshot wound was obviously the cause of death,

516
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:55,370
但同时有肺痨的明显迹象
but there are clear indicators of consumption.

517
00:20:55,370 --> 00:20:56,710
还是验一下尸吧
It might be worth a postmortem.

518
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:58,610
我们需要所有能收集到的线索
We need all the information we can get.

519
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:01,620
老爸一走  他就开始显摆观察力了
Oh, isn't he observant, now that Daddy's gone

520
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:08,820
我在某些方面观察力确实很强
I am observant in some ways,

521
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:12,330
就像福尔摩斯在某些方面没有眼力见一样
just as Holmes is quite blind in others.

522
00:21:12,780 --> 00:21:15,170
-是吗  -没错
- Really? - Yes, really.

523
00:21:16,690 --> 00:21:20,930
为了混进男人的天下  也是蛮拼的啊
Amazing...what one has to do to get ahead in a man's world.

524
00:21:29,690 --> 00:21:31,180
他这话什么意思
What's he saying that for?

525
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,390
干你的活儿去
Get back to work!

526
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:44,260
说吧  福尔摩斯  你肯定有些想法吧
Well, Holmes? Surely you must have some theory?

527
00:21:44,260 --> 00:21:45,460
还没有
Not yet.

528
00:21:46,050 --> 00:21:49,430
此案非常复杂  华生  很棘手
These are deep waters, Watson, deep waters.

529
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:53,760
但我还得继续深入
And I shall have to go deeper still.

530
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:05,050
几个月后  我们才又继续
It was not for several months that we were to pick up

531
00:22:05,060 --> 00:22:07,530
调查这件奇案
the threads of this strange case again.

532
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:11,630
还是在出乎意料的情况之下
And then under very unexpected circumstances.

533
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:15,360
现在已经五起案子了  每起都一样
Five of them now, all the same, every one of them.

534
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,900
请安静  这件事事关重大
Hush, please, this is a matter of supreme importance.

535
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,760
-什么  -黄赤交角
- What is? - The obliquity of the ecliptic.

536
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:20,900
我必须要理解它
I have to understand it.

537
00:22:21,020 --> 00:22:21,590
什么东西
What is it?

538
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:23,960
不知道  我还在努力弄懂它
I don't know, I'm still trying to understand it.

539
00:22:24,020 --> 00:22:25,670
-我以为你无所不知  -当然不是了
- I thought you understood everything. - Of course not,

540
00:22:25,670 --> 00:22:27,260
那多浪费我大脑的记忆空间
that would be an appalling waste of brain space.

541
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:28,310
我是专攻类型的
I specialise.

542
00:22:28,330 --> 00:22:29,580
这事为什么重要
And what's so important about this?

543
00:22:29,580 --> 00:22:31,740
五起无聊的谋杀案又怎么重要了
What's so important about five boring murders?

544
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:34,220
这可不无聊  五个男人被害
They're not boring. Five men dead,

545
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,730
死在家中  地上洒满了生米
murdered in their own homes, rice on the floor

546
00:22:36,730 --> 00:22:37,540
就像在婚礼上一样
like at a wedding,

547
00:22:37,540 --> 00:22:40,390
墙上用血着"你"
and the word "You" written in blood on the wall!

548
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:44,080
是她  那个鬼新娘
It's, it's her, it's the Bride.

549
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:46,100
她又复活了
Somehow she's risen again.

550
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,010
解决了
Solved it.

551
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:49,410
你怎么就破案了
You can't have solved it!

552
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:51,210
我当然破了  非常简单
Of course I've solved it, it's perfectly simple.

553
00:22:51,210 --> 00:22:52,860
神秘的瑞克莱蒂太太事件
The incident of the mysterious Mrs Ricoletti,

554
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:54,090
这位来自阴间的凶手
the killer from beyond the grave,

555
00:22:54,090 --> 00:22:55,830
被媒体大肆渲染
has been widely reported in the popular press.

556
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:58,060
现在有人将自己实施的谋杀
Now people are disguising their own dull little murders

557
00:22:58,060 --> 00:22:59,280
伪装成是鬼魂杀人
as the work of a ghost,

558
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:02,200
借此迷惑愚蠢的苏格兰场
to confuse the impossibly imbecilic Scotland Yard.

559
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,450
瞧  我破案了
There you are, solved.

560
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:05,150
你走前跟赫德森太太聊一下
Pay Mrs Hudson a visit on your way out,

561
00:23:05,150 --> 00:23:06,700
她喜欢有参与感
she likes to feel involved.

562
00:23:06,910 --> 00:23:07,810
你确定
You sure?

563
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:09,450
确定  你走吧
Certainly. Go away.

564
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:11,280
华生  我准备好了
Watson! I'm ready.

565
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:13,690
戴好帽子穿好鞋  我们有个重要约会
Your hat and boots, we have an important appointment.

566
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:17,480
华生医生几个月前不是搬走了吗
Didn't Dr Watson move out a few months ago?

567
00:23:18,410 --> 00:23:19,640
他确实搬走了  对吧
He did, didn't he?

568
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:22,190
那我一直是在跟谁说话来着
Who have I been talking to all this time?

569
00:23:22,590 --> 00:23:25,670
我代表愚蠢至极的苏格兰场说一句
Well, speaking on behalf of the impossibly imbecilic Scotland Yard,

570
00:23:25,670 --> 00:23:27,390
那张椅子上没人
that chair is definitely empty.

571
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,010
确实没人吧
It is, isn't it?

572
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,650
但我这些日子过得挺不错的
Works surprisingly well, though.

573
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:34,520
我还以为他有进步了
I actually thought he was improving.

574
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:12,000
你去哪了
Where have you been?

575
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,800
抱歉  老爷  我今早有些迟了
Sorry, sir, I'm rather behind my time this morning.

576
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,810
你连蛋都不会煮吗
Are you incapable of boiling an egg?!

577
00:24:16,620 --> 00:24:19,240
炉里没有火  到处是灰尘
The fires are rarely lit, there is dust everywhere

578
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:22,080
你清理我靴子上的泥时差点毁了那双鞋
and you almost destroyed my boots scraping the mud off them.

579
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:24,300
如果不是我妻子掌管佣人的事
If it wasn't my wife's business to deal with the staff,

580
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:25,430
我会亲自管教你
I would talk to you myself.

581
00:24:25,430 --> 00:24:26,620
我妻子人呢
Where is my wife?

582
00:24:26,730 --> 00:24:28,570
很抱歉  老爷  夫人出去了
Begging your pardon, sir, but the mistress has gone out.

583
00:24:28,570 --> 00:24:29,940
这么早就出门了吗
Out? At this hour of the morning?

584
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:31,960
是的  老爷  您不知道吗  老爷
Yes, sir. Did you not know that, sir?

585
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:34,130
她去哪了  她最近总出去
Where did she go? She's always out these days.

586
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:36,620
您不也是  老爷
Not unlike yourself...sir.

587
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:37,740
什么
I'm sorry...?

588
00:24:38,260 --> 00:24:40,050
-就是说说我的观察  老爷  -够了
- Just observing, sir. - Well, that's quite enough,

589
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:41,250
谁让你观察的
nobody asked you to be observant.

590
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:42,140
抱歉  老爷  我就是说
Sorry, sir, I just meant

591
00:24:42,140 --> 00:24:44,160
你们很少一起待在家里了
you're hardly ever home together any more, sir.

592
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,550
你的言行近乎无礼
You are dangerously close to impertinence.

593
00:24:46,550 --> 00:24:49,020
我要跟我妻子谈下  让她管教下你了
I shall have a word with my wife to have a word with you.

594
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:52,920
好  老爷  那您什么时候见她呢
Very good, sir. And when will you be seeing her?

595
00:24:54,290 --> 00:24:56,060
-听着...  -我差点忘了  老爷
- Now, listen... - Oh, I nearly forgot, sir.

596
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:58,190
-有封您的电报  -你忘了
- A telegram came for you. - You forgot?!

597
00:24:58,190 --> 00:24:59,650
没有  只是差点忘了
No, I nearly forgot.

598
00:24:59,650 --> 00:25:01,050
你一上午都在干什么
What have you been doing all morning?

599
00:25:01,050 --> 00:25:03,160
读您《斯特兰德月刊》上的新文章  老爷
Reading your new one in The Strand, sir.

600
00:25:04,050 --> 00:25:05,190
你喜欢吗
Did you enjoy it?

601
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:06,830
您为什么从不提我  老爷
Why do you never mention me, sir?

602
00:25:06,830 --> 00:25:07,680
下去吧
Go away.

603
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:26,640
-什么的什么  -黄赤交角
- The what of the what? - The obliquity of the ecliptic.

604
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:29,020
你说"速来"  我以为是很重要的事
"Come at once," You said. I assumed it was important.

605
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:31,590
是很重要  那是地球的赤道面
It is. It's the inclination of the earth's equator

606
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,940
与其绕太阳运行的轨道平面的夹角
to the path of the sun on the celestial plane.

607
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:35,690
你是刚学的吧
You been swotting up?

608
00:25:35,690 --> 00:25:37,040
-我为什么要这么做  -为了显得聪明
- Why would I do that? - To sound clever.

609
00:25:37,050 --> 00:25:39,260
-我本就聪明  -我懂了
- I am clever. - Oh, oh, I see.

610
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:40,540
懂什么了
You see what?

611
00:25:40,910 --> 00:25:44,950
我推理我们是要去见某个比你聪明的人
I deduce we're on our way to see someone cleverer than you.

612
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:47,240
闭嘴
Shut up.

613
00:26:58,050 --> 00:26:59,020
什么
Sorry, what?

614
00:27:17,330 --> 00:27:21,290
对想研究人类的人来说  这里最合适
To anyone who wishes to study mankind, this is the spot.

615
00:27:21,290 --> 00:27:23,180
也很方便  毕竟你那不断扩张的屁股
Handy really, as your ever-expanding backside

616
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:24,420
永远粘在了这里
is permanently glued to it.

617
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:25,390
早上好  我的哥哥  
Good morning, brother mine.

618
00:27:25,390 --> 00:27:27,620
夏洛克  华生医生
Sherlock. Dr Watson.

619
00:27:28,740 --> 00:27:30,370
您看上去  很不错  先生
You look...well, sir.

620
00:27:30,370 --> 00:27:32,860
真的吗  我觉得我看上去很巨大
Really? I rather thought I looked enormous.

621
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:35,700
既然您提到了  这种程度的暴饮暴食
Well, now you mention it, this level of consumption

622
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:39,190
对您的健康危害极大
is incredibly injurious to your health.

623
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:41,070
-您的心脏  -不用担心那个  华生
- Your heart... - No need to worry on that score, Watson.

624
00:27:41,070 --> 00:27:44,190
-不吗  -那个器官只会待在一个宽敞的地方
- No? - There's only a large cavity where that organ should reside.

625
00:27:44,190 --> 00:27:47,030
-家族通病  -我不是故意说话尖刻
- It's a family trait. - Oh, I wasn't being critical.

626
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:48,260
如果您继续这样  先生
If you continue like this, sir,

627
00:27:48,260 --> 00:27:50,420
我觉得您最多能活五年
I give you five years at the most.

628
00:27:50,430 --> 00:27:52,520
五年  我们觉得也就是三年  
Five? We thought three,

629
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,490
对吧  夏洛克
did we not, Sherlock?

630
00:27:53,490 --> 00:27:54,630
我还是倾向于四年
I'm still inclined to four.

631
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:57,320
还是这样  你看到了却不懂观察
As ever, you see but you do not observe.

632
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:59,170
注意我眼白的颜色发生了变化
Note the discolouration in the whites of my eyes,

633
00:27:59,180 --> 00:28:01,480
角膜周围出现可见的脂肪圈
the visible rings of fat around the corneas.

634
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:02,740
你是对的  我改赌三年
Yes, you're right. I'm changing my bet to three years,

635
00:28:02,740 --> 00:28:04,330
-四个月零十一天  -打赌
- four months and 11 days. - A bet?!

636
00:28:04,330 --> 00:28:05,980
我理解你不赞同  华生
I understand your disapproval, Watson,

637
00:28:06,090 --> 00:28:07,210
但他好胜心强
but if he's feeling competitive,

638
00:28:07,210 --> 00:28:09,260
可以自己控制早点死亡
it's perfectly within his power to die early.

639
00:28:09,260 --> 00:28:10,980
这也是要冒的风险
That's a risk you'll have to take.

640
00:28:11,420 --> 00:28:12,730
你在拿自己的性命打赌
You're gambling with your own life?

641
00:28:12,730 --> 00:28:15,750
为什么不  比拿别人的命打赌有意思多了
Why not? It's so much more exciting than gambling with others'.

642
00:28:15,750 --> 00:28:17,680
整三年  如果你吃了那个葡萄干布丁的话
Three years flat - if you eat that plum pudding!

643
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:18,230
就这么定了
Done.

644
00:28:24,610 --> 00:28:28,160
我以为几天前会因为领主庄园的案子见到你呢
I expected to see you a few days ago about the Manor House case.

645
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:30,170
我觉得那案子你会有点力不从心
I thought you might be a little out of your depth there.

646
00:28:30,170 --> 00:28:31,590
没有  我解决了
No. I solved it.

647
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:34,080
-肯定是亚当斯  -是亚当斯
- It was Adams, of course. - Yes, it was Adams.

648
00:28:34,090 --> 00:28:35,580
嫉妒杀人
Murderous jealousy.

649
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:38,060
他给皇家天文学会写了一篇
He'd written a paper for the Royal Astronomical Society

650
00:28:38,060 --> 00:28:40,230
关于黄赤交角的论文
on the obliquity of the ecliptic,

651
00:28:40,230 --> 00:28:41,330
然后又读到另一篇
and then read another

652
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:42,930
比他写的好的
that seemed to surpass it.

653
00:28:42,930 --> 00:28:43,890
我知道  我读了
I know, I read it.

654
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:45,170
你看明白了吗
Did you understand it?

655
00:28:45,220 --> 00:28:47,540
我当然明白了  很浅显易懂
Yes, of course I understood it, it was perfectly simple.

656
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:49,940
不是  你明白嫉妒杀人吗
No, did you understand the murderous jealousy?

657
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:51,240
一个伟大的大脑
It is no easy thing

658
00:28:51,250 --> 00:28:54,450
去考虑一个更伟大的大脑可不容易
for a great mind to contemplate a still greater one.

659
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,330
你召我来就是为了羞辱我吗
Did you summon me here just to humiliate me?

660
00:28:58,330 --> 00:28:59,460
是的
Yes.

661
00:28:59,460 --> 00:29:02,060
当然不是  但这是最大的乐趣
Of course not, but it is by far the greater pleasure.

662
00:29:02,060 --> 00:29:03,640
那你能不能解释下为什么要召
Then would you mind explaining exactly why you did summon...?

663
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:06,820
我们的生活方式受到了一个无形敌人的威胁
Our way of life is under threat from an invisible enemy.

664
00:29:07,130 --> 00:29:09,930
他们每天都常伴我们身边
One that hovers at our elbow on a daily basis.

665
00:29:10,220 --> 00:29:11,900
这些敌人无处不在
These enemies are everywhere...

666
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:13,810
无人发现
undetected...

667
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:16,430
无法阻止
and unstoppable.

668
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:17,790
社会主义者
Socialists?

669
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:20,320
不是社会主义者  医生  不是
Not socialists, Doctor, no.

670
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:21,590
-无政府主义者  -不是
- Anarchists? - No.

671
00:29:21,590 --> 00:29:23,960
法国人  妇女参政权论者
The French? The suffragists?

672
00:29:24,260 --> 00:29:26,760
还有什么大规模团体是你不担心的吗
Is there any large body of people you're not concerned about?

673
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:29,720
华生医生永远心怀警惕  详说
Dr Watson is endlessly vigilant. Elaborate...

674
00:29:29,720 --> 00:29:31,060
不  去调查
No. Investigate.

675
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:33,700
这是我的推测  我需要你去证实
This is a conjecture of mine, I need you to confirm it.

676
00:29:33,700 --> 00:29:35,280
我给你个案子
I'm sending you a case.

677
00:29:35,290 --> 00:29:37,290
-苏格兰人  -苏格兰人
- The Scots? - The Scots?!

678
00:29:37,550 --> 00:29:39,310
你是否知道最近
Are you aware of recent theories concerning

679
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,740
关于妄想症的理论
what is known as paranoia?

680
00:29:40,740 --> 00:29:42,360
听着像是塞尔维亚人
Oh, sounds Serbian.

681
00:29:42,650 --> 00:29:45,280
会有个女人去找你  卡迈克夫人
A woman will call on you. Lady Carmichael.

682
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:46,650
你得接她的案子
I want you to take her case.

683
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:48,560
但这些敌人  如果你不告诉我们
But these enemies, how are we to defeat them

684
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:49,930
我们怎么打败他们
if you won't tell us about them?

685
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:51,770
我们不会打败他们  
We don't defeat them.

686
00:29:51,770 --> 00:29:53,840
我们几乎绝对要输给他们
We most certainly lose to them.

687
00:29:54,340 --> 00:29:55,320
为什么
Why?

688
00:29:57,440 --> 00:30:00,800
因为他们是正确的  我们是错的
Because they are right. And we are wrong.

689
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:03,830
卡迈克夫人的案子  是什么
Lady Carmichael's case, what is it?

690
00:30:03,830 --> 00:30:06,360
放心  会有值得你注意的地方
Rest assured, it has features of interest.

691
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:08,610
-我从没这么说过  -你真说过
- I never really say that. - You really do.

692
00:30:08,850 --> 00:30:10,200
我估计你已经解决了
And you've solved it already, I assume?

693
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:14,320
只是设想而已  我要你去跑腿
Only in my head. I need you for the, er, legwork.

694
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:16,100
为什么不告诉我们你的答案
Why not just tell us your solution?

695
00:30:16,110 --> 00:30:17,940
那还有什么意思呢
And where would be the sport in that?

696
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:19,410
你愿意接吗  夏洛克
Will you do it, Sherlock?

697
00:30:19,410 --> 00:30:21,990
这绝对是极好的消遣
I can promise you a superior distraction.

698
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,460
我有一个条件  你再吃一个葡萄干布丁
On one condition. Have another plum pudding.

699
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:25,740
本来就准备吃了
There's one on the way.

700
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:27,360
两年十一个月四天
Two years, 11 months and four days.

701
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:31,820
开始好玩喽  滴答  滴答  滴答
Ha, it's getting exciting now! Ticktock, ticktock, ticktock.

702
00:30:35,350 --> 00:30:37,330
谢谢  怀尔德
Thank you, Wilder.

703
00:30:37,330 --> 00:30:40,300
有一位梅尔斯先生要见你  福尔摩斯先生
Also, a Mr Melas to see you, Mr Holmes.

704
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:43,510
等我五分钟  我还有一场赌局要赢呢
Give me five minutes, I have a wager to win.

705
00:30:46,170 --> 00:30:48,890
还是十五分钟吧
Better make that 15.

706
00:30:50,230 --> 00:30:51,640
滴答
Ticktock.

707
00:30:55,300 --> 00:30:57,790
福尔摩斯先生  我是来请您出主意的
Mr Holmes, I have come here for advice.

708
00:30:57,900 --> 00:31:00,040
-这个不难  -还有您的帮助
- That is easily got. - And help.

709
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:01,510
这就未必容易了
Not always so easy.

710
00:31:01,910 --> 00:31:06,110
有古怪的事发生了  福尔摩斯先生
Something has happened, Mr Holmes, something...unusual

711
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:08,670
而且很可怕
and...terrifying.

712
00:31:08,670 --> 00:31:09,970
那你真是太幸运了
Then you are in luck.

713
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:10,970
幸运吗
Luck?!

