00:41:16,100 --> 00:41:17,840
会把他拖进地狱
of the late Mrs Ricoletti.

891
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,190
这太荒谬了  不是吗
That's a lot of nonsense, isn't it?

892
00:41:22,190 --> 00:41:24,080
老天  是啊  你的左轮手枪带了吗
God, yes. Did you bring your revolver?

893
00:41:24,080 --> 00:41:25,530
手枪在幽灵面前有什么用
What good would that be against a ghost?

894
00:41:25,530 --> 00:41:27,240
-对极了  你带了吗  -当然了
- Exactly. Did you bring it? - Yeah, of course.

895
00:41:27,240 --> 00:41:28,990
那就来吧  华生  来吧
Then come, Watson, come.

896
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:30,770
游戏开始了
The game is afoot.

897
00:41:39,840 --> 00:41:43,120
-蹲下  华生  老天爷  -抱歉  抽筋了
- Get down, Watson, for heaven's sake! - Sorry. Cramp.

898
00:41:46,470 --> 00:41:48,810
-灯还亮着吗  -是的
- Is the lamp still burning? - Yes.

899
00:41:52,060 --> 00:41:53,560
尤斯塔斯爵士的灯灭了
There goes Sir Eustace.

900
00:41:55,380 --> 00:41:57,160
卡迈克夫人的也灭了
And Lady Carmichael.

901
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,980
宅子睡下了
The house sleeps.

902
00:42:02,740 --> 00:42:05,130
老天  这是我这辈子最漫长的一夜了
Hmm, good God, this is the longest night of my life.

903
00:42:05,130 --> 00:42:07,030
耐心点  华生
Have patience, Watson.

904
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:10,200
才到午夜
Only midnight.

905
00:42:12,210 --> 00:42:15,450
我们很少这样坐在一起
You know, it's rare for us to sit together like this.

906
00:42:15,550 --> 00:42:18,210
希望如此  我们在等待谋杀案
I should hope so. It's murder on the knees.

907
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:24,110
两个老朋友说着话  聊着天
Two old friends just talking. Chewing the fat.

908
00:42:24,870 --> 00:42:26,410
男人对男人
Man-to-man.

909
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,050
非凡的女人
So, a remarkable woman.

910
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:34,940
-谁  -卡迈克夫人
- Who? - Lady Carmichael.

911
00:42:34,940 --> 00:42:36,880
女性是你的专长  华生
The fair sex is your department, Watson.

912
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:37,940
你说什么就是什么
I'll take your word for it.

913
00:42:37,980 --> 00:42:40,350
你挺喜欢她  "她有着少见的洞察力"
Well, you liked her. "A woman of rare perception."

914
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:41,970
和美妙的高足弓
And admirably high arches.

915
00:42:41,980 --> 00:42:43,750
她一进房间  我就注意到了
I noticed them as soon as she stepped into the room.

916
00:42:43,750 --> 00:42:45,990
-她太好了  他配不上  -你这么认为吗
- Huh, she's far too good for him. - You think so?

917
00:42:45,990 --> 00:42:47,630
不  是你这么认为  我看得出来
No. You think so. I could tell.

918
00:42:48,020 --> 00:42:49,650
恰恰相反  我对此毫无看法
On the contrary, I have no view on the matter.

919
00:42:49,650 --> 00:42:50,750
不  你有
Yes, you have.

920
00:42:52,980 --> 00:42:55,270
婚姻不是我会思考的问题
Marriage is not a subject upon which I dwell.

921
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:57,030
-为什么  -你今晚是怎么回事
- Oh, why not? - What's the matter with you this evening?

922
00:42:57,030 --> 00:43:00,410
你戴的那块表  里面有张照片
That watch that you're wearing, there's a photograph inside it.

923
00:43:00,410 --> 00:43:03,990
我瞥过一眼  我想那是艾琳·阿德勒
I glimpsed it once. I believe it is of Irene Adler.

924
00:43:04,030 --> 00:43:06,030
你不只是瞥了一眼  你是等我睡着了
You didn't glimpse it, you waited till I'd fallen asleep

925
00:43:06,030 --> 00:43:07,930
-才拿去看的  -是这样没错
- and looked at it. - Yes, I did.

926
00:43:07,930 --> 00:43:10,610
-你真以为我不会发现吗  -艾琳·阿德勒
- You seriously thought I wouldn't notice? - Irene Adler.

927
00:43:10,990 --> 00:43:12,920
一位强大的对手  一次了不起的冒险
Formidable opponent, a remarkable adventure.

928
00:43:12,950 --> 00:43:14,890
-一张漂亮的照片  -你为什么要谈这些
- A very nice photograph. - Why are you talking like this?

929
00:43:14,890 --> 00:43:16,370
你为什么坚决要独身
Why are you so determined to be alone?

930
00:43:16,370 --> 00:43:17,610
你没事吧  华生
Are you quite well, Watson?

931
00:43:17,620 --> 00:43:18,950
这问题就这么奇怪吗
Is it such a curious question?

932
00:43:18,950 --> 00:43:20,350
对于维也纳精神病医生来说  不奇怪
From a Viennese alienist, no.

933
00:43:20,350 --> 00:43:22,740
对于退役的军医来说  当然奇怪
From a retired army surgeon, most certainly.

934
00:43:22,900 --> 00:43:26,510
福尔摩斯  我是毫无竞争对手的
Holmes, against absolutely no opposition whatsoever,

935
00:43:26,510 --> 00:43:29,230
-你最亲密的朋友  -我承认
- I am your closest friend. - I concede it.

936
00:43:29,490 --> 00:43:31,740
我现在是想和你
I am currently attempting to have a perfectly

937
00:43:31,790 --> 00:43:33,120
再正常不过地交谈
normal conversation with you.

938
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:34,190
别这样
Please don't.

939
00:43:34,190 --> 00:43:36,790
你为什么非要独身
Why do you need to be alone?

940
00:43:37,180 --> 00:43:39,070
如果你指的是感情纠葛  华生
If you are referring to romantic entanglement, Watson,

941
00:43:39,070 --> 00:43:41,730
恐怕你就是  正如我以前常说过的
which I rather fear you are, as I have often explained before,

942
00:43:41,990 --> 00:43:43,860
我憎恶一切感情
all emotion is abhorrent to me.

943
00:43:44,540 --> 00:43:46,670
感情是干扰灵敏仪器的沙粒
It is the grit in a sensitive instrument.

944
00:43:46,870 --> 00:43:48,920
-镜片上的裂纹  -镜片上的裂纹  对
- The crack in the lens. - The crack in the lens. Yes.

945
00:43:48,920 --> 00:43:50,120
这就是了
Well, there you are, you see,

946
00:43:50,120 --> 00:43:52,200
-我之前都说过  -不  这都是我写的
- I've said it all before. - No, I wrote all that.

947
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:54,210
你在援引《斯特兰德月刊》中你自己的话
You're quoting yourself from The Strand Magazine.

948
00:43:54,210 --> 00:43:55,040
说得对
Well, exactly.

949
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:57,580
那些是我的话  不是你的
Those are my words, not yours!

950
00:43:57,850 --> 00:44:00,740
那是我向公众展示的你
That is the version of you that I present to the public.

951
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:04,170
没有感情的头脑  计算机器
The brain without a heart. The calculating machine.

952
00:44:04,170 --> 00:44:06,070
那些都是我写的  福尔摩斯
I write all of that, Holmes,

953
00:44:06,070 --> 00:44:08,590
读者们也欣然接受  但我不相信
and the readers lap it up. But I do not believe it.

954
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:09,890
我非常想给你的编辑写信
Well, I've a good mind to write to your editor.

955
00:44:09,900 --> 00:44:11,410
你是一个活生生的人
You are a living, breathing man.

956
00:44:11,510 --> 00:44:14,070
-你也有生活  也有过去  -有什么
- You've lived a life, you have a past. - A what?!

957
00:44:14,070 --> 00:44:15,950
-你肯定有过...  -有什么
- Well, you must have had... - Had what?

958
00:44:18,170 --> 00:44:19,410
-你懂的  -不懂
- You know. - No.

959
00:44:21,190 --> 00:44:22,400
经历
Experiences.

960
00:44:22,550 --> 00:44:25,000
把左轮手枪递给我  我突然需要用一下
Pass me your revolver, I have a sudden need to use it.

961
00:44:25,010 --> 00:44:26,800
见鬼  福尔摩斯  你也是血肉之躯
Damn it, Holmes, you are flesh and blood,

962
00:44:26,810 --> 00:44:28,660
也有感情  你有...
you have feelings, you have...

963
00:44:28,660 --> 00:44:31,830
你肯定有...冲动
You must have... impulses.

964
00:44:31,830 --> 00:44:33,490
天啊  我从未如此盼望
Dear Lord, I have never been so impatient

965
00:44:33,490 --> 00:44:35,260
被杀人不眨眼的鬼魂攻击
to be attacked by a murderous ghost.

966
00:44:35,260 --> 00:44:39,390
作为你的朋友  作为担心你的人
As your friend, as someone who worries about you...

967
00:44:41,100 --> 00:44:42,510
是什么让你变成这样的
What made you like this?

968
00:44:44,610 --> 00:44:45,940
华生...
Oh, Watson...

969
00:44:47,830 --> 00:44:49,630
没什么塑造了我
Nothing made me.

970
00:44:51,670 --> 00:44:53,200
我塑造了自己
I made me.

971
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:56,030
红胡子
Redbeard?

972
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:57,910
我的天啊
Good God!

973
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:05,510
我们该怎么办
What are we to do?

974
00:45:09,910 --> 00:45:11,280
我们去跟她聊聊吧
Why don't we have a chat?

975
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:20,080
是瑞克莱蒂太太吧
Mrs Ricoletti, I believe!

976
00:45:21,060 --> 00:45:23,100
就这个时节来说  真是宜人的一晚
A pleasant night for the time of year, is it not?

977
00:45:23,140 --> 00:45:25,200
这不可能  福尔摩斯  不可能
It cannot be true, Holmes, it cannot!

978
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:26,240
是不可能
No, it can't.

979
00:45:36,190 --> 00:45:37,920
-锁上了  -按照要求锁着
- Is it locked? - As per instruction.

980
00:45:37,950 --> 00:45:39,230
那是打破窗户的声音  是吗
That was a window breaking, wasn't it?

981
00:45:39,230 --> 00:45:41,450
我们只需要担心一扇打破的窗户
There's only one broken window we need concern ourselves with.

982
00:45:52,800 --> 00:45:54,330
-待在这儿  华生  -什么  不
- Stay here, Watson. - What? No.

983
00:45:54,330 --> 00:45:56,210
进出房子所有的门窗都锁着
All the doors and windows to the house are locked.

984
00:45:56,260 --> 00:45:58,100
这是他们唯一的出口  我需要你在这儿守着
This is their only way out, I need you here!

985
00:45:58,100 --> 00:45:59,090
但那声音很接近了
But the sound was so close.

986
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:01,290
-肯定是从房子这一侧传来的  -守在这儿
- It had to be from this side of the house. - Stay here!

987
00:46:15,760 --> 00:46:17,120
不
No!

988
00:46:24,640 --> 00:46:27,770
你答应过保护他安全的  你答应过的
You promised to keep him safe. You promised!

989
00:46:28,580 --> 00:46:29,870
你...
You...

990
00:46:53,450 --> 00:46:55,230
你是人  我知道的
You're human, I know that.

991
00:46:58,400 --> 00:46:59,600
你肯定是
You must be.

992
00:47:03,790 --> 00:47:07,690
我们这样站在黑暗中也没什么用
Little use us standing here in the dark.

993
00:47:09,050 --> 00:47:12,540
毕竟  这是十九世纪
After all, this is the 19th century.

994
00:47:53,050 --> 00:47:57,270
别忘了我
Do not forget me!

995
00:47:57,910 --> 00:48:02,620
别忘了我
Do not forget me!

996
00:48:09,290 --> 00:48:11,470
-华生  -她在那儿  她就在那边
- Watson! - She's there! She's down there!

997
00:48:11,470 --> 00:48:12,860
别告诉我你擅离职守了
Don't tell me you abandoned your post!

998
00:48:12,860 --> 00:48:14,710
什么  福尔摩斯  她在那儿  我看见她了
What? Holmes, she's there, I saw her!

999
00:48:18,990 --> 00:48:20,360
没人了  都怪你
Empty, thanks to you!

1000
00:48:21,300 --> 00:48:22,480
煮熟的鸭子飞了
Our bird is flown!

1001
00:48:22,490 --> 00:48:25,040
不  福尔摩斯  不是你想的那样
No! No, Holmes, it wasn't what you think.

1002
00:48:25,040 --> 00:48:26,390
我看见她了  鬼魂
I saw her! The ghost!

1003
00:48:26,390 --> 00:48:28,830
根本没有鬼魂
There are no ghosts!

1004
00:48:32,300 --> 00:48:35,270
发生什么了  尤斯塔斯爵士在哪
What happened? Where is Sir Eustace?

1005
00:48:37,350 --> 00:48:38,520
死了
Dead.

1006
00:48:42,040 --> 00:48:44,030
你不能怪自己
You really mustn't blame yourself, you know.

1007
00:48:45,420 --> 00:48:46,520
是  你说得对
No, you're quite right.

1008
00:48:47,180 --> 00:48:48,430
很高兴你在逐渐开悟
I'm glad you're seeing sense.

1009
00:48:48,430 --> 00:48:49,680
华生也应该受谴责
Watson is equally culpable.

1010
00:48:49,940 --> 00:48:52,050
我们搞砸了整个案子
Between us, we've managed to botch this whole case.

1011
00:48:52,070 --> 00:48:53,810
我做出承诺  要保护那个人
I gave an undertaking to protect that man,

1012
00:48:53,820 --> 00:48:55,580
结果他现在胸口插着匕首  倒在那里
now he's lying there with a dagger in his breast.

1013
00:48:55,580 --> 00:48:58,080
其实  你承诺的是调查他的谋杀案
In fact, you gave an undertaking to investigate his murder.

1014
00:48:58,080 --> 00:49:00,320
满怀没这个必要的自信
In the confident expectation I would not have to!

1015
00:49:03,000 --> 00:49:04,480
你能告诉我们什么吗  医生
Anything you can tell us, Doctor?

1016
00:49:05,240 --> 00:49:08,720
凶手刺杀他的力度可不小
Well, he's been stabbed with considerable force.

1017
00:49:08,810 --> 00:49:09,990
这么说  是男性
It's a man, then?

1018
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:11,910
可能是
Possibly.

1019
00:49:11,910 --> 00:49:14,760
刀刃非常锋利  也可能是女性
A very keen blade, so it could conceivably have been a woman?

1020
00:49:14,760 --> 00:49:15,820
从理论上说  是的
In theory, yes,

1021
00:49:15,820 --> 00:49:17,470
但我们知道是谁  我看见她了
but we know who it was, I saw her.

1022
00:49:17,470 --> 00:49:19,450
-华生  -我看见鬼魂了  亲眼所见
- Watson! - I saw the ghost, with my own eyes!

1023
00:49:19,450 --> 00:49:21,500
你什么也没看见  你看到了别人演的
You saw nothing! You saw what you were supposed to see!

1024
00:49:21,500 --> 00:49:23,340
你自己说过的  我没有想象力
You said yourself, I have no imagination.

1025
00:49:23,340 --> 00:49:25,410
那就动动脑  去掉不可能的情况
Then use your brain, such as it is, to eliminate the impossible,

1026
00:49:25,410 --> 00:49:26,770
在这桩案子中就是鬼魂
which in this case is the ghost,

1027
00:49:26,780 --> 00:49:29,010
并且观察余下的  就此而言  就是答案
and observe what remains, which in this case is a solution

1028
00:49:29,010 --> 00:49:31,550
十分明显  就连雷斯垂德也能想明白
so blindingly obvious even Lestrade could work it out!

1029
00:49:31,640 --> 00:49:32,430
谢谢
Thank you!

1030
00:49:32,430 --> 00:49:34,440
别去想什么来自冥界的幽灵了
Forget spectres from the other world!

1031
00:49:34,730 --> 00:49:37,460
只有一个嫌疑人有作案动机和机会
There is only one suspect with motive and opportunity.

1032
00:49:37,550 --> 00:49:38,730
他们简直与留了字条无异
They might as well have left a note.

1033
00:49:38,730 --> 00:49:39,930
他们确实留下了字条
They did leave a note.

1034
00:49:39,990 --> 00:49:41,990
然后还有另一扇破窗的问题
And then there's the matter of the other broken window.

1035
00:49:41,990 --> 00:49:44,800
-什么另一扇破窗  -说得对  根本没有
- What other broken window? - Precisely! There isn't one.

1036
00:49:44,800 --> 00:49:47,330
唯一一扇破窗就是我和华生进来的那扇
The only broken window is the one that Watson and I entered through,

1037
00:49:47,340 --> 00:49:49,390
但在那之前  我们清楚地听见了声音...
yet, prior to that, we distinctly heard the sound of...

1038
00:49:49,390 --> 00:49:51,020
-你刚才说什么  -你说什么
- What did you just say? - Sorry?

1039
00:49:51,470 --> 00:49:53,140
关于字条  你刚才说什么
About a note, what did you just say?

1040
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:55,800
-我说凶手确实留下了字条  -不  没有
- I said the murderer DID leave a note. - No, they didn't.

1041
00:49:55,890 --> 00:49:58,640
匕首上系了张字条  你肯定看见了
There's a message tied to the dagger. You must have seen it!

1042
00:49:58,640 --> 00:49:59,740
-没有什么字条  -有的
- There's no message. - Yes!

1043
00:49:59,740 --> 00:50:01,520
我发现尸体的时候上面没有字条
There was no message when I found the body.

1044
00:50:18,940 --> 00:50:19,820
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

1045
00:50:23,870 --> 00:50:24,810
上面写了什么
What is it?

1046
00:50:43,410 --> 00:50:44,620
你想吗
Do you?

1047
00:50:45,370 --> 00:50:46,530
我想什么
Do I what?

1048
00:50:49,590 --> 00:50:51,510
你怎么拿到这个的
H-how did you get that?

1049
00:50:51,510 --> 00:50:53,690
我把它留在犯罪现场了
I left it at the crime scene.

1050
00:50:54,140 --> 00:50:55,350
犯罪现场
"Crime scene"?

1051
00:50:55,590 --> 00:50:58,300
你从哪学来的这些词汇
Where do you pick up these extraordinary expressions?

1052
00:50:58,430 --> 00:50:59,650
你想他吗
Do you miss him?

1053
00:51:00,040 --> 00:51:01,490
莫里亚蒂已经死了
Moriarty is dead.

1054
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:02,880
但是
And yet...?

1055
00:51:04,560 --> 00:51:06,460
我们没找到他的尸体
His body was never recovered.

1056
00:51:06,880 --> 00:51:10,820
一个被推下瀑布的数学教授是该找不到
To be expected when one pushes a maths professor over a waterfall.

1057
00:51:11,210 --> 00:51:14,040
纯粹理性被惊险的情节推翻
Pure reason toppled by sheer melodrama.

1058
00:51:14,040 --> 00:51:15,610
一句话概括了你的生活
Your life in a nutshell.

1059
