你曾说你的大脑是块硬盘
You once called your brain a hard drive.

1602
01:21:15,940 --> 01:21:18,070
跟病毒打个招呼吧
Well, say hello to the virus.

1603
01:21:18,720 --> 01:21:20,740
这就是我们的结局  你和我
This is how we end, you and I.

1604
01:21:21,600 --> 01:21:22,780
总是在这里
Always here,

1605
01:21:23,650 --> 01:21:24,950
总是你和我一起
always together.

1606
01:21:27,350 --> 01:21:30,330
你的脑子很不错  莫里亚蒂
You have a magnificent brain, Moriarty.

1607
01:21:30,650 --> 01:21:31,960
我很敬佩
I admire it.

1608
01:21:32,550 --> 01:21:35,770
我认为它甚至可能与我相当
I concede it may even be the equal of my own.

1609
01:21:36,170 --> 01:21:37,240
我很感动
I'm touched.

1610
01:21:39,830 --> 01:21:40,890
我很荣幸
I'm honoured.

1611
01:21:41,440 --> 01:21:43,820
但说到在悬崖边缘
But when it comes to the matter of unarmed combat

1612
01:21:43,830 --> 01:21:45,750
徒手搏斗
on the edge of a precipice...

1613
01:21:47,250 --> 01:21:48,870
你等着入水吧
You're going in the water,

1614
01:21:49,730 --> 01:21:51,370
小个子
short-arse.

1615
01:22:03,570 --> 01:22:06,330
你觉得自己高大威猛吗  夏洛克
Oh, you think you're so big and strong, Sherlock!

1616
01:22:06,330 --> 01:22:07,490
在我面前可不是
Not with me.

1617
01:22:20,710 --> 01:22:22,560
我是你的弱点
I am your weakness!

1618
01:22:24,670 --> 01:22:25,990
我能打倒你
I keep you down!

1619
01:22:27,670 --> 01:22:31,270
每次你失足  每次你失败
Every time you stumble, every time you fail,

1620
01:22:31,480 --> 01:22:33,070
每当你势弱
when you're weak,

1621
01:22:33,190 --> 01:22:34,820
我都
I...am...

1622
01:22:35,540 --> 01:22:36,460
在那儿
there!

1623
01:22:39,150 --> 01:22:39,980
不
No,

1624
01:22:40,580 --> 01:22:41,930
别抵抗
don't try to fight it.

1625
01:22:42,140 --> 01:22:44,030
躺好  认输吧
Lie back and lose!

1626
01:22:49,630 --> 01:22:51,220
我们一起跳下去吧
Shall we go over together?

1627
01:22:52,040 --> 01:22:53,710
必须是我们一起  是吧
It has to be together, doesn't it?

1628
01:22:53,710 --> 01:22:56,460
到最后  永远是你
At the end it's always just you

1629
01:22:56,970 --> 01:22:58,290
和我
and me!

1630
01:23:04,250 --> 01:23:06,580
教授  麻烦你离我朋友远点
Professor, if you wouldn't mind stepping away from my friend,

1631
01:23:06,580 --> 01:23:10,590
我相信  他有点反感你的纠缠
I do believe he finds your attention a shade annoying.

1632
01:23:12,810 --> 01:23:14,560
这不公平  你们二对一
That's not fair, there's two of you!

1633
01:23:15,770 --> 01:23:18,090
我们总是两个人  你不看《斯特兰德月刊》吗
There's always two of us. Don't you read The Strand?

1634
01:23:20,110 --> 01:23:21,660
跪下  教授
On your knees, Professor.

1635
01:23:25,980 --> 01:23:28,770
手背到头后
Hands behind your head.

1636
01:23:29,480 --> 01:23:30,530
谢谢你  约翰
Thank you, John.

1637
01:23:32,740 --> 01:23:34,200
你什么时候开始叫我约翰了
Since when do you call me John?

1638
01:23:35,430 --> 01:23:36,790
你肯定想不到
You'd be surprised.

1639
01:23:37,020 --> 01:23:38,000
未必
No, I wouldn't.

1640
01:23:40,830 --> 01:23:42,320
你该醒来了  夏洛克
Time you woke up, Sherlock.

1641
01:23:44,410 --> 01:23:46,480
我是个讲故事的  我分得出自己是在故事里
I'm a story-teller, I know when I'm in one.

1642
01:23:46,920 --> 01:23:47,990
当然
Of course.

1643
01:23:48,770 --> 01:23:50,300
当然了  约翰
Of course you do, John.

1644
01:23:51,180 --> 01:23:52,260
他什么样
So what's he like?

1645
01:23:53,030 --> 01:23:55,360
另一个世界的我
The other me in the other place?

1646
01:23:56,340 --> 01:23:57,910
比看上去聪明
Smarter than he looks.

1647
01:23:58,160 --> 01:23:59,540
那一定很聪明了
Pretty damn smart, then.

1648
01:24:00,950 --> 01:24:02,300
很聪明
Pretty damn smart.

1649
01:24:02,380 --> 01:24:05,940
你俩直接私奔得了
Ugh, why don't you two just elope, for God's sake?!

1650
01:24:06,300 --> 01:24:07,520
无礼
Impertinent.

1651
01:24:08,310 --> 01:24:09,370
过分
Offensive.

1652
01:24:09,590 --> 01:24:12,050
其实  你介意吗
Actually, would you mind?

1653
01:24:12,330 --> 01:24:13,300
完全不
Not at all.

1654
01:24:23,020 --> 01:24:24,840
-本来就该我了  -是啊
- It was my turn. - Quite so.

1655
01:24:25,580 --> 01:24:27,580
你打算怎么醒过来
So how do you plan to wake up?

1656
01:24:30,900 --> 01:24:32,210
就这样吧
I should think like this.

1657
01:24:34,100 --> 01:24:34,990
你确定吗
Are you sure?

1658
01:24:35,940 --> 01:24:38,630
偷偷告诉你  约翰  坠落是杀不死我的
Between you and me, John, I always survive a fall.

1659
01:24:39,150 --> 01:24:39,970
可你是怎么做到
But how?

1660
01:24:41,870 --> 01:24:43,660
很简单的  亲爱的华生
Elementary, my dear Watson.

1661
01:25:15,800 --> 01:25:17,660
-想我了吗  -夏洛克  你没事吧
- Miss me? - Sherlock, are you all right?

1662
01:25:17,660 --> 01:25:19,370
是的  当然  我怎么会有事呢
Yes. Of course I am, why wouldn't I be?

1663
01:25:19,370 --> 01:25:21,620
因为你可能刚服药过量  你该入院
Because you probably just OD'd. You should be in hospital.

1664
01:25:21,620 --> 01:25:22,790
没时间了
Hm, no time.

1665
01:25:23,490 --> 01:25:26,100
我得赶紧去贝克街  莫里亚蒂回来了
I have to go to Baker Street now, Moriarty's back.

1666
01:25:26,690 --> 01:25:28,360
我都希望他是真回来了
I almost hope he is,

1667
01:25:29,080 --> 01:25:30,590
如果能让你不再沉迷于此
if it'll save you from this.

1668
01:25:32,810 --> 01:25:34,090
现在用不着这个了
No need for that now,

1669
01:25:34,770 --> 01:25:35,770
我有真正好玩的了
I've got the real thing.

1670
01:25:35,770 --> 01:25:37,900
-我有工作了  -夏洛克
- I have work to do. - Sherlock...

1671
01:25:39,360 --> 01:25:40,340
答应我
..Promise me.

1672
01:25:42,480 --> 01:25:43,720
你还站这儿干什么
What are you still doing here?

1673
01:25:43,720 --> 01:25:45,620
你不是该去帮我搞个赦免还是什么的吗
Shouldn't you be off getting me a pardon or something,

1674
01:25:45,620 --> 01:25:47,140
像个好大哥那样
like a proper big brother?

1675
01:25:52,630 --> 01:25:53,670
华生医生
Dr Watson...

1676
01:25:58,130 --> 01:25:59,220
照顾好他
Look after him.

1677
01:26:01,030 --> 01:26:01,840
拜托
Please.

1678
01:26:22,860 --> 01:26:24,380
夏洛克  等等  解释一下
Sherlock, hang on, explain.

1679
01:26:24,640 --> 01:26:25,860
莫里亚蒂还活着吗
Moriarty's alive, then?

1680
01:26:25,860 --> 01:26:28,090
我没说他活着  我说他回来了
I never said he was alive, I said he was back.

1681
01:26:28,180 --> 01:26:29,310
那么他死了吗
So he's dead?

1682
01:26:29,470 --> 01:26:30,130
他当然死了
Of course he's dead,

1683
01:26:30,130 --> 01:26:32,260
他开枪爆了自己的头  不可能活下来
he blew his own brains out, no-one survives that.

1684
01:26:32,790 --> 01:26:35,170
我刚刚为了证明这点而服药过量
I just went to the trouble of an overdose to prove it.

1685
01:26:36,270 --> 01:26:39,070
莫里亚蒂死了  毫无疑问
Moriarty is dead, no question.

1686
01:26:40,170 --> 01:26:44,170
但更重要的是  我很清楚他接下来要做什么
But more importantly, I know exactly what he's going to do next.

1687
01:26:54,370 --> 01:26:55,560
飞行机
Flying machines,

1688
01:26:55,560 --> 01:26:57,830
还有什么...电话
these, er, telephone contraptions?

1689
01:26:57,840 --> 01:26:59,800
这是什么疯狂的幻想啊
What sort of lunatic fantasy is that?

1690
01:26:59,800 --> 01:27:00,870
只是我对
It was simply my conjecture

1691
01:27:00,870 --> 01:27:02,360
未来世界
of what a future world might look like

1692
01:27:02,370 --> 01:27:04,790
和你我在其中角色的猜想
and how you and I might fit inside it.

1693
01:27:05,160 --> 01:27:07,190
一个逻辑学家应该可以从一滴水
From a drop of water a logician should be able to infer

1694
01:27:07,190 --> 01:27:09,690
推断出是大西洋还是尼亚加拉河
the possibility of an Atlantic or a Niagara.

1695
01:27:09,690 --> 01:27:11,070
或是莱辛巴赫瀑布
Or a Reichenbach?

1696
01:27:11,370 --> 01:27:13,920
-你把这桩案子写好了吗  -是的
- Have you written up your account of the case? - Yes.

1697
01:27:15,280 --> 01:27:16,360
经过修改把它写成了
Modified to put it down as

1698
01:27:16,360 --> 01:27:19,040
-罕见的我未能破案的案例了吧  -当然
- one of my rare failures, of course? - Of course.

1699
01:27:22,210 --> 01:27:23,610
《无形军队
The Adventure Of...

1700
01:27:24,090 --> 01:27:25,590
历险记》
The Invisible Army.

1701
01:27:27,320 --> 01:27:28,650
或者愤怒军团
The League Of Furies?

1702
01:27:29,670 --> 01:27:31,160
恐怖军团
The Monstrous Regiment?

1703
